# Implementation Plan - visual Rubrical Audit Remediation (Images 143-146)

This session completes the visual audit of Part 3 (Menaion) of the Dolnytsky Typikon, advancing through the end of August. Discrepancies were identified in the transition between July 31 (Forefeast) and August 1 (Procession of the Cross) where structural text and footnote anchors were missing or desynchronized compared to the 2010 Lviv edition (Images 143-144). Additionally, a massive block of redundant footnotes at the end of the Menaion file will be removed.

## Proposed Changes

### [Menaion Part 3 Remediation]

#### [MODIFY] [Final_Dolnytsky_part3_menaion.txt](file:///e:/Google%20Antigravity/Projects/Translation/Final/Final_Dolnytsky_part3_menaion.txt)

- **July 31 Matins (Line 2385)**: Correct the Sessional hymn rule. The physical source (Image 143) specifies the Sessional hymn is "of the Cross" (Хреста), not "of the Forefeast". Anchor `[^452]` will be correctly placed.
- **July 31 Liturgy (Line 2388)**: Restore the full Liturgy rubrics for the Procession of the Cross/Forefeast. The current generic summary will be replaced with the detailed physical text from Page 143, including the blessing of water and herbs and footnote anchor `[^453]`.
- **July 31 Sunday Rule (Line 2390)**: Restore the missing sentence regarding the Procession, Veneration, and Blessing of Water on Sunday, including footnote anchor `[^451]`.
- **Cleanup (Lines 2469-2654)**: Delete the redundant block of footnotes 279-465. These are already present in the authoritative `Final_footnotes.txt` and their presence in the Menaion file is a structural error that displaces the natural end of the part.

